Description: Baas, SaaS, Financial solution
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: Whillet is a new generation fintech solution. It provides embedded finance services allowing clients to open digital wallets for their users and to manage them using application programming interface (API) integration. As a BaaS provider, Whillet handles all licensing requirements, relieving the client of that responsibility.     The fintech solution from Whillet enables across the board installation and support for all processes. This includes websites, apps, marketplaces and other platforms set up for client users, facilitating such things as bank accounts, electronic money accounts and bonus accounts.   Customer wallets can be accessed in a variety of ways, such as via a mobile app or through a website. The embedded finance technology allows clients to substantially increase revenue and improve unit economy indicators.   A good example of how Whillet works is by employing multilevel processing solutions for loyalty programs while, simultaneously, partners get easy management of customized loyalty programs, thereby rewarding regular users with bonuses and real money which they can spend on further purchases.   Multi-billing facilities enable payments to be distributed among all participants in the sales process - the customer, suppliers, store (or site), couriers, and so on. This automated system saves companies time for pursuing more important strategic tasks.   A branded, customized wallet can include any methods of depositing and withdrawing money that the customer chooses. Debit and credit cards, mobile payments, e-money, transfer money providers, and so on. All of the above will be provided as an integrated link in the customer's account. Whillet's prime focus is on the B2B and B2C markets. The company works with marketplaces, sharing platforms, retail chains of various sizes, car dealerships, insurance and travel companies, postal service providers, contractor-user and production-delivery-customer models, car parkings, fines payments, license acquisitions, online stores, freelance exchanges, taxi companies, and gas stations - the list of possible uses just goes on and on.   Whillet, based in Palo Alto, California, has a highly professional team with experience of serving more than 2000 partners worldwide - that’s over 30 million open wallets and more than 10 million transactions carried out each and every day.

Description: Contract Lifecycle and Contract Change Lifecycle Management SaaS software for complex US federal procurement programs
Headquarters Regions: Greater San Diego Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: nGAP Incorporated was founded in 2008 to produce innovative software procurement solutions with a particular focus on Federal Government requirements.  Since our founding, much has happened to change how the government needs to do business and how they should use technology to effect these changes.  Speed in developing important features is critical.  The new mantra is; make it useful today; make it perfect tomorrow.  Features are required that set new standards, like getting programs done on schedule and budget. These new challenges have meant that we need to understand our customers – their missions, their jargon, and their problems. It requires a group of extraordinary people who understand what it takes to be successful. We bring together the expertise necessary to succeed; we know our customers, and we have learned how to apply our technology to their problems.    At our beginning, we sought to make comprehensive acquisition lifecycle management solutions, and we have done this with the Open Acquisition System (OAS).  But we found out by listening to our customers that something important was missing that no one was addressing.  The need was contract management that supports large-scale programs by managing substantial amounts of data as an integrated system that serves a multitude of stakeholders.  nGAP does this now! nGAP TODAY Today nGAP is composed of highly skilled Subject Matter Experts, teams of highly specialized software engineers, business analysts, and researchers focused exclusively on the challenges of acquisition system automation and improvement and bringing state-of-the-art innovation to the Federal Government contracting process. nGAP’s latest innovation is called Open Concurrent Contract Modification (OCCM). OCCM is designed as a module of the OAS platform. The OCCM Module automates the change management process for large weapon platform maintenance programs inside the DOD. These large platforms include U.S. Navy Assets such as carriers, submarines, and destroyers; U.S. Air Force flight platforms and U.S. Army assets with long lifecycles that require significant maintenance and sustainment budgets.   nGAP currently offers a machine learning-based data processing, formatting, and export API microservices. The service is designed to constantly ingest, transform, and analyize technical data derived from common forms and documents.

Headquarters Regions: Dallas/Fort Worth Metroplex, Southern US
Full Description: Evoplugs is an innovative electric vehicle (EV) charging company that has emerged as a key player in the rapidly evolving EV industry. Since its inception, Evoplugs has been dedicated to building a robust charging infrastructure that promotes sustainability and accelerates the adoption of electric vehicles worldwide. Let's explore the history of Evoplugs, from its humble beginnings to its current position as a leading EV charging firm. Evoplugs was founded in 2013 by a team of passionate entrepreneurs who recognized the growing need for convenient and accessible EV charging solutions. In its early years, Evoplugs focused on research and development, working tirelessly to design innovative charging stations that offered superior performance, reliability, and user-friendliness. The company collaborated with various industry experts, engineers, and EV enthusiasts to create a robust charging infrastructure tailored to the evolving needs of EV owners. Building on its early successes, Evoplugs began deploying charging stations across strategic locations, targeting major metropolitan areas, commercial hubs, and public spaces. By forming strategic partnerships with shopping malls, office complexes, and municipalities, Evoplugs ensured that their charging infrastructure was accessible to EV owners where they needed it the most. These partnerships played a crucial role in expanding Evoplugs' market presence and driving customer adoption. During this period, Evoplugs focused on enhancing its charging technology and diversifying its product offerings. The company introduced fastcharging solutions capable of delivering high power levels, reducing charging times significantly. Evoplugs also developed smart charging systems that utilized advanced algorithms and data analytics to optimize charging efficiency and minimize the strain on the electrical grid. These technological advancements positioned Evoplugs as an industry leader in providing cutting-edge EV charging solutions. With EV adoption gaining momentum worldwide, Evoplugs embarked on an ambitious global expansion strategy. The company entered into partnerships with international EV manufacturers, enabling seamless integration of Evoplugs charging stations with their vehicles. This integration allowed for enhanced vehicle-to-grid capabilities, bidirectional charging, and improved user experience. Evoplugs also expanded its operations into new regions, establishing a strong presence In recent years, Evoplugs has focused on developing an extensive charging network, allowing EV owners to access charging infrastructure seamlessly across different countries and charging providers. Evoplugs Network, a information on the availability, location, and compatibility of Evoplugs charging stations. The company also introduced membership plans, offering EV owners exclusive benefits and discounted charging rates. Evoplugs: Pioneering the Future of Electric Vehicle Charging Early Years: 2013-2015: Laying the Foundation: 2016-2017: Market Expansion and Partnerships: 2018-2019: Technological Advancements: 2020-2021: Global Expansion and Integration in Asia, and North America. 2022-Present: Evoplugs Network and Future Vision: user-friendly website, was launched, providing real-time Looking ahead, Evoplugs envisions a future where electric vehicles dominate the roads and sustainable transportation becomes the norm. The company continues to invest in research and development, exploring advancements such as wireless charging, ultra-fast charging, and renewable energy integration. Evoplugs remains committed to revolutionizing the EV charging experience and contributing to a greener and more sustainable world. Evoplugs' remarkable journey mirrors the broader trajectory of the EV industry, and their dedication to innovation and customer satisfaction has propelled them to the forefront of the charging infrastructure landscape. As the world embraces electric mobility, Evoplugs stands ready to power the future of transportation with its reliable and cutting-edge charging solutions.

Description: Peprotech develops and produces recombinant cytokine products for life-science research.

Full Description: PeproTech was established in 1988 by a group of scientists who decided to focus their efforts on the development and production of recombinant cytokines for life-science research. These products are distributed worldwide through customer-service offices in the US, UK, France, Germany, Israel, Korea, China, Japan, Brazil, and Mexico. Description: They've blended everything from rake handles to golf balls and glow sticks in their test lab.
Headquarters Regions: Western US
Full Description: Back in 1975, Tom's curiosity was piqued when he used a vacuum to clean up some spilled wheat kernels. His innate inquisitiveness drove him to revolutionize the home wheat milling industry, taking it from stone grinding to his patented stainless steel milling heads. Like most inventors, Tom didn't stop there. He envisioned the perfect mixer using the freshly milled flour from his mill to make wholesome bread in minutes. When back in the lab, Tom developed an autoknead feature, enabling the mixer to knead the dough, develop the gluten and turn off automatically when finished. Tom continued to improve the mixer and decided to add a blender with a square jar, rather than the conventional round jar. As Tom expanded his mill and mixer business, new ideas developed. He enhanced the blender and began developing commercial blending machines just as the smoothie era began. Fast forward a few decades to the present: Tom is still inventing and the company is still growing! Walking into the world of Blendtec, you'll find the innovative engineering team and their "torture chamber, " you'll see the international team preparing for where their travels will take them next, and you'll glimpse Tom scooting off to blend up his next invention.
Industry Groups: Consumer Electronics, Consumer Goods, Hardware, Other

Description: DevFactory is a development company of factory sofware.
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: DevFactory provides a complete enterprise grade continuous integration and code coverage tool along with test case creation and automation services through its aLine product. -- Today, DevFactory manages over 100 million lines of code in over a hundred product code bases from industries as diverse as financial services, network management and engineering services. DevFactory is able to deliver superior results at significantly lower prices because of its radical delivery model – the software factory. What is a Software Factory?  A software factory is a new way to develop and maintain enterprise applications. Instead of traditional, expensive time and materials based approaches, the software factory relies on extensive standardization and automation to reduce costs and improve results.  The fundamental premise behind the software factory is that many enterprise application maintenance/development can be done using standard service types. Enterprises can now complete common maintenance tasks by “ordering” a specified number of each of these services. This level of standardization lends itself to automation – another key tenet of the factory. Development, testing, acceptance and integration processes are completely automated using standardized tools thereby eliminating manual processes. Software automation and specialized teams execute each service type systematically, lowering costs and increasing success rates.
